                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      BJP meet to focus on Bihar polls
                            
	Patna, May 23 (PTI): A two-day national executive meeting of the BJP would be held here from June 12 to discuss strategy for the Assembly elections in Bihar due later this year.        
	Senior party leaders L.K. Advani, leader of Opposition in the Lok Sabha Sushma Swaraj, her Rajya Sabha counterpart Arun Jaitley, president Nitin Gadkari among other leaders would attend the meet, BJP general secretary Dharmendra Pradhan said today.        
	Pradhan and party general secretary (organisation) Ram Lal reviewed the preparations for the meet attended among others by state BJP president C.P. Thakur, deputy chief minister Sushil Kumar Modi and state ministers Nand Kishore Yadav and Ashwani Kumar Choubey.        
	Asked whether Gujarat chief minister Narendra Modi would also attend the meeting, Pradhan said all the BJP chief ministers would be there. We selected Patna for the meet as the Assembly polls will take place later this year and we have to formulate a comprehensive plan to ensure that the NDA, led by Nitish Kumar, stages a come back, he said.        
	Other national issues, which would come up for discussion, were escalating prices and alleged failure of the UPA government at the Centre to curb Maoist violence.        
	A rally at Gandhi Maidan on June 13 would be addressed by senior BJP leaders.                                                                                                                                                          
